You know what causes bugs in C (besides memory leaks)?  Complex or clever expressions that don&#x27;t reveal their semantics at first glance.  As an example from elsewhere in the thread:<p><pre><code>    return (x > y) - (x < y);
</code></pre>
Quick.  What&#x27;s that do?<p>What will the next person who looks at the code think it does?
